events.name: Silent Walking Meditation & Pranic Breathing
events.description:
"Speech is Silver, Silence is Golden".

Calling all those beings who wish to enjoy nature's beauty, witness their inner calmness, and experience mindfulness. :)

We will begin our journey with a peaceful walking meditation for a while or so, thereafter find a calm place to sit down and relax. During this time, we will practice Nadi-Shodhana Pranayama (most potent style of breath-work based on ancient technique of Pranic Breathing).
Then we will have some food, mingle and share our experience with each other (30 min approx.).
In the end, we will head back to Universitet (train station).

The purpose of this event is to:
Be a silent witness to all that you experience inside and outside.
Feel peace and gratitude while you walk.
Build up the muscle of your focus and energy level with the breathing techniques.

NOTE:

-Start Time: 10:30 A.M. - 12:30 A.M.

-Please be on time - 10:30 A.M.

-Meeting point - near the exit from Universitet train station.

-The date may change if the weather is bad.

-The exact track will be chosen closer to the event.

-It is recommended to observe silence and not to talk during the walk, unless too necessary!

-You will be guided how to do Pranayama.

-This event will be hosted by VegePal, Jyotika who is a decade old -practitioner of Yoga & Meditation.

Fun Fact: "Pranayama" is a Sanskrit word and means "Controlling the movement of Breath". "Pran" means breath, life-force, life-energy or the vital source of our energy; "Ayama" means control.

You should have:

• Comfortable shoes
• Enough water (around 1 liter)
• Some food
• Mat or sheet to sit upon

Let me know if you have any further questions.

Strength, skill, focus, and flexibility: these are the keys of success for a samurai warrior.
This traditional Japanese martial art (450 years old) is not what you have experiences before in Sweden.
It tests your physique and develops your mind and spirit.

We are now opening up for a limited number of beginners!

Great for increasing leg and arm power, mental focus, body control, courage & explosive power.
Kenjutsu is the art of fighting an opponent with the sword - we do it full contact, but have no fear.

It being so different from other traditional martial arts is that it was the household school of the Shogun, demanding strength, skill and intellect.

All equipment is provided to you by us. You are welcome to join in your usual workout clothes.
No indoor shoes required.

Beginners are given a total of two free sessions at our school.
1000kr for full membership, 500 for late joiners.

We teach in Swedish, Japanese, English and German.

events.name: 5 Days - Stockholm 2 Nights and 2 Nights in Copenhagen
events.description:
A succinct stay in two Scandinavian cities, Stockholm and Copenhagen settings for Scandi-crime drama The Bridge. A weekend break to look forward to over the Bank Holiday.

Stockholm, the capital of Sweden, encompasses 14 islands and more than 50 bridges on an extensive Baltic Sea archipelago. The cobblestone streets and ochre-colored buildings of Gamla Stan (the old town) are home to the 13th-century Storkyrkan Cathedral, the Kungliga Slottet Royal Palace and the Nobel Museum, which focuses on the Nobel Prize. Ferries and sightseeing boats shuttle passengers between the islands.

Next up Denmark’s delightful capital city. Be like a local and hop on a bicycle or explore on foot, wandering past picturesque squares and green copper-roofed towers to the fabulous Botanical Gardens. Be sure to take in the National Museum of Denmark and the quirky community of Christiania, packed with striking homes, lively bars and organic eateries. Find exceptional cuisine at Noma, which has been consistently labelled the world's best restaurant.

Departing from Gatwick 9.20 am arrival at 12.40 in Stockholm
Depart Copenhagen at 21.00 arrive to Gatwick at 22.05

Itinerary

Day 1 - Friday 1 st May

On arrival in Stockholm, transfer to your hotel for check-in.
Lets explore what Stockholm has to offer with a 2 Day Pass for several activities including hop on hop of bus tour, walking tour, visit to the Sweden’s Royal Palace and more

Day 2 - Saturday 2nd May

After breakfast let's explore Stockholm’s closest archipelago as we cruise to the island of Fjäderholmarna. Take a walk through the town’s colorful streets and artisan shops, we can stay as long as we like, and enjoy some of the island's charming restaurants. Find out more here https://www.shermanstravel.com/advice/day-trip-from-stockholm-fjaderholmarna-island/

Day 3 Sunday 3rd May

We check out from our hotel and embark on a scenic train ride to Copenhagen. We will stay for 2 nights

After checking in, we will explore the town with the Copenhagen City Card (including free public transport) in the entire Copenhagen region. We will receive discounts at participating restaurants and activities enjoy free or discount entrance at more than 80 museums and attractions, includes hop-on hop-off sightseeing boat/bus at leisure and journey along the idyllic canals and waterways of the city centre. Admire the old houses and new buildings at your own pace, Discover interesting neighbourhoods, such as the historic Nyhavn district and many more.

Day 4 - Monday 4th May

Continue explore the city with your Copenhagen City Card

Day 5 Tuesday 5th May
Last day
Free time to explore, possibly Optional day trip to Malmo which is less then 1 hr from Copenhagen

events.name: Yin Yoga med Mentala Strategier

group.name: Yeshe Norbu Mind Training Centre - Stockholm

events.description:
https://yeshenorbu.se/events/yin-yoga-med-mentala-strategier-2/

Yin yoga är en långsam typ av yoga som innefattar principer från traditionell kinesisk medicin med asanas (positioner) som man vilar i under en längre stund. I den här kursen kombineras klassisk Yin Yoga med utvecklandet av mentala strategier (gynnsamma förhållningssätt) från den buddhistiska traditionen. Dessa är närvaro, acceptans, vänlighet, tålamod, icke-dömande, glädje och förmågan att släppa taget.

Vad kommer jag att lära mig?

I kursen lär vi oss att möta det som händer under yogan med de olika mentala strategierna (som exempelvis acceptans eller vänlighet). Det kan vara i mötet med ett fysiskt motstånd i kroppen, med tankar som far iväg någon annanstans, med utmaningen i att stanna i en position så länge som 3 minuter. Hur kan jag möta allt detta på ett varmt, öppet och tillåtande sätt?

För att komma åt bindväven behöver vi stanna länge i varje position, 3-5 minuter. På så sätt mjukar vi upp bindväven och blir rörliga och flexibla. Man kan också säga att du genom yin yogan genomför en slags akupunktur på dig själv, genom att fokusera på de spänningar och de motstånd som dyker upp i kroppen, andas in i dessa och släppa taget.
Kursen är på svenska.

Vad kommer jag att ta med mig?

Genom att medvetet arbeta på detta sätt i ett yin yoga pass skapar vi förutsättningar för att även börja agera på liknande sätt utanför yogasalen. Nya nervbanor har skapats i hjärnan, nya möjligheter öppnar sig i livet. I yin yogan arbetar vi med bindväven eller med fascian, det nätverk utan början eller slut som omsluter i princip allt i kroppen från muskler och skelett, till organ och celler.

Yin är motsatsen till yang, yang driver utveckling och vill framåt, större, bättre, längre, starkare. Yin yogan hjälper dig att öppna upp slappna av, släppa taget och komma till ro, det finns ingen strävan, ingen perfekt ställning, inget mål. Bara du och din kropp precis där ni är just nu. Det är bara att stanna kvar och andas.

Lärare

Kristina Spegel

Kristina är leg psykolog, yin yoga och meditationslärare med egen träning sedan 15 år. Kristina är också certifierad i CBMT/ Corporate Bases Mindfulness Training och håller till vardags föreläsningar och utbildningar runt om i Sverige i detta med fokus på meditationsträning och de mentala strategierna, närvaro, vänlighet, tålamod, icke-dömande och glädje.

Kristinas lärare i urval: Magdalena Mecweld, Kent Nyström, Jon Kabat Zinn, Stephan Pende, Glenn Svensson, Roshi Joan Hallifax m.fl.

events.name: Remote work hierarchy of needs: more than just using digital tools
events.description:
Remote work needs are similar to Maslow’s famous model of the hierarchy of human needs. You need the basis - the internet, to connect people digitally (VPN, too!). Then you need the tools for collaboration.

What companies are slowly starting to realize is that tools are only the tip of the iceberg. Policies and processes come next. It will take a few more weeks to see that even that is not enough. People still burn out, feel lonely, don’t collaborate effectively, don’t lead their teams to success.

To make the whole pyramid stable you need to support and empower your key people through things like micro-coaching, communities of practice and constantly monitoring the state of the company."

Learning outcomes:
Explore policies, processes, and employee support systems that need to be implemented in the company if you want to survive the long remote winter.
Introduce the concept of remote micro-coaching and how the participants can apply it in their own companies.
Set an intention for the first baby step towards improving organizational processes and commit to it.

About Dima Syrotkin:
I lead a Finnish called Panda Training. We provide human-led and chatbot micro-coaching to employees via Teams/Slack to empower key people, facilitate communities of practice and use data to diagnose processes and employee wellbeing. Working with clients like Universal Pictures, SAP, Bayer.

events.description:
https://yeshenorbu.se/events/tara-meditation-och-kriya-tantra/
I Tara-meditation används flera sinnen, bland annat mantra-recitation och visualisering, vilket har en helt annan dynamik än t.ex. mindfulness-meditation. Tara-meditation är en mycket populär och viktig form av meditation i den Tibetansk Buddhistiska traditionen.

VAD KOMMER JAG ATT LÄRA MIG?
För mer erfarna meditatörer, som kanske redan har introducerats till Tara, så är det här en möjlighet att fördjupa relationen med Tara och utforska nya perspektiv på Buddhistisk tantrisk meditation.

VAD TAR JAG MED MIG I MITT DAGLIGA LIV?

MER OM KURSEN
Rob Preece, skapare av denna kurs, hämtade sin inspiration från åratal av studier och praktik under Lama Yeshe. Lama Yeshe uppmuntrade Rob att fortsätta utveckla och konkretisera sina tankar om att integrera buddistisk och västerländsk psykolog för att bereda vägen för våra västerländska sinnen.

Om du vill delta i kursen är första eller andra tillfället obligatoriskt. Vi erbjuder heller ingen drop-in utan deltagare måste göra ett åtagande att gå hela kursen.

FÖRKUNSKAPER
Kursen kräver inga förkunskaper av just denna typ av meditation, men förutsätter att man accepterar Buddhismens tre juveler (Buddha, Dharma och Sangha). Det är inte en introduktion till meditation i sig och därför inte lämplig om man inte har någon tidigare har någon erfarenhet av meditation.

LÄRARE
Jens Näsström, Psykolog.

Jens har studerat med Rob Preece flera år, och nu har Rob har i sin tur auktoriserat och uppmuntrat honom att lära ut den här formen av meditation på Yeshe Norbu.

Jens har ett livslångt intresse för religionspsykologi och har mediterat i den tibetanska traditionen i över femton år.

How to choose which initiatives or projects to start?

How to coordinate the activities of multiple teams working on those initiatives? Are there (and are there always) dependencies?

How to monitor how things are progressing? How can we adapt to market and technological situations that change continuously and sometimes dramatically?

And then we need to address the usual questions: how long will this project last? How much will it cost?

Traditional approaches have serious problems when it comes to answering these questions. The variability and uncertainty of the current context put them in great difficulty. «Oh, but now there are agile methodologies. Problem solved, right? " The bad news is that no, the solution is not just having agile teams and less than ever adopting a scaling framework.

Let's talk about it. And let's see what approaches we can use to answer those questions.

Register by using the following link: https://agile42.zoom.us/webinar/register/7615846060696/WN_hM_UDTLyS9yhqG0QzJBfqA

You will get a confirmation email with instructions on how to join the webinar.

The event will be hosted by Gaetano Mazzanti from agile42.

events.name: Acceptans och tålamod – vägen till inre ro
events.description:
Acceptans och tålamod – vägen till inre ro | onsdagar 18:00 – 19:15
4 veckor från 15 april

Vi vill alla må bra och njuta av livet – helst hela tiden. Vi tror att vi kan bli lyckliga genom att ändra på externa saker i vårt liv, t.ex. arbetar mindre, tränar mer, byter bostad, håller oss friska osv. På samma sätt tänker vi att vi blir oroliga, rädda eller stressade beroende på saker som kommer utanför oss själva – en person, en situation eller som just nu ett virus med allt vad det medför.

Buddha förklarade att den faktiska orsaken till våra problem och våra obehagliga känslor är våra negativa tankesätt. Genom meditation kan vi lära oss att acceptera både det som pågår runt omkring oss samt den oro och frustration vi känner inombords. Med hjälp av tålamod och acceptans utvecklar vi en inre styrka som hjälper oss att lösa våra problem och finnas till för andra. På denna kurs kommer vi att träna i praktiska meditationstekniker och positiva tankesätt som vi kan använda varje dag för att hitta ro i denna utmanande tid.

group.name: Yeshe Norbu Mind Training Centre - Stockholm

events.description:
https://yeshenorbu.se/events/tara-meditation-och-kriya-tantra/
I Tara-meditation används flera sinnen, bland annat mantra-recitation och visualisering, vilket har en helt annan dynamik än t.ex. mindfulness-meditation. Tara-meditation är en mycket populär och viktig form av meditation i den Tibetansk Buddhistiska traditionen.

VAD KOMMER JAG ATT LÄRA MIG?
För mer erfarna meditatörer, som kanske redan har introducerats till Tara, så är det här en möjlighet att fördjupa relationen med Tara och utforska nya perspektiv på Buddhistisk tantrisk meditation.

VAD TAR JAG MED MIG I MITT DAGLIGA LIV?

MER OM KURSEN
Rob Preece, skapare av denna kurs, hämtade sin inspiration från åratal av studier och praktik under Lama Yeshe. Lama Yeshe uppmuntrade Rob att fortsätta utveckla och konkretisera sina tankar om att integrera buddistisk och västerländsk psykolog för att bereda vägen för våra västerländska sinnen.

Om du vill delta i kursen är första eller andra tillfället obligatoriskt. Vi erbjuder heller ingen drop-in utan deltagare måste göra ett åtagande att gå hela kursen.

FÖRKUNSKAPER
Kursen kräver inga förkunskaper av just denna typ av meditation, men förutsätter att man accepterar Buddhismens tre juveler (Buddha, Dharma och Sangha). Det är inte en introduktion till meditation i sig och därför inte lämplig om man inte har någon tidigare har någon erfarenhet av meditation.

LÄRARE
Jens Näsström, Psykolog.

Jens har studerat med Rob Preece flera år, och nu har Rob har i sin tur auktoriserat och uppmuntrat honom att lära ut den här formen av meditation på Yeshe Norbu.

Jens har ett livslångt intresse för religionspsykologi och har mediterat i den tibetanska traditionen i över femton år.

events.name: Foundations of Mindfulness, 8 week course - ONLINE and at the centre

group.name: Yeshe Norbu Mind Training Centre - Stockholm

events.description:
https://yeshenorbu.se/events/foundations-of-mindfulness-8-week-course-april-2020/

We will offer this course ONLINE and also in person at the centre on Roslagsgatan 62.

EVENT DETAILS
Mindfulness is the basis of all mind training. Only with a relaxed, focused, and clear mind can we develop any of the other positive qualities of the mind. In these times of almost infinite distractions, stress, and scattered attention it is also, more than ever, the foundation for mental well-being, resilience, and happiness. Foundations of Mindfulness is our most popular course, for good reasons.

WHAT WILL I LEARN
This course comprises eight sessions designed to provide a clear framework for the practice of cultivating mindfulness – the practice of cultivating a calm, clear & focused mind.

The course is part of our MSC Meditation Program and mindfulness forms the basis for developing the other mental qualities taught in the selflessness and compassion programs. The MSC Meditation program was developed by the world-renowned meditation teacher Glen Svensson based on the work of of Dr. Alan Wallace.

The program has eight sessions:

Relaxation
Focus
Clarity
Observing Thoughts
Resting in Stillness
Stillness in Motion
Open Awareness
Mindfulness in Daily Life

WHAT WILL I TAKE AWAY INTO MY DAILY LIFE
Ability to approach all situations in life with a more relaxed, focused, balanced and clear mind.
A greater degree of self-awareness and understanding of your own emotions, reactions, thoughts, and feelings.
Less reactivity, the ability respond instead of just react.
A greater sense of ease and well-being.
Less distraction, not be so easily caught up in multitasking and scattered attention.
The foundation of more self-care and self-compassion.
The foundation for more care, concern, and compassion towards others.

TEACHER
Martin Ström

Martin is the founder and director of Yeshe Norbu Mind Training Centre. For almost 20 years he’s been on a mission to understand more about the mind, both from a western neuro scientific and an eastern contemplative perspective.

Martin is a licensed CBT Psychologist and has practiced meditation for almost two decades. He is also a graduate of the two-year program Foundation of Buddhist Thought. Among other things, Martin has taught mindfulness in the corporate world as a accredited trainer of Corporate Based Mindfulness Training. He is also the co-author of three books; Fokus på jobbet in Swedish, and I’m Sorry You Were Saying and The Mind of The Leader in English.

MORE ABOUT THIS COURSE
Course material is The Attention Revolution by Alan Wallace (sold at the centre).

--------------------------
Vajrasattva is the embodiment of the purifying powers of the Buddha. Its practice enables us to cleanse all the negativities we have accumulated in countless lives and thus avoid their results of suffering and obstacles.

Vajrasattva Practice is not only about reciting mantras and visualization, but it is about purifying our minds. In the Vajrasattva Practice, we do the practice of Four Opponent Powers, which is a psychological process of purifying nonvirtous imprints on the mindstream.

They are: 1) the power of the object, taking refuge in the Three Rare Sublime Ones and generating bodhicitta; 2) the power of regret, feeling deep regret for the negativity committed; 3) the power of resolve, determining not to repeat that negativity; and 4) the power of remedy, a practice such as Vajrasattva that effectively acts as an antidote to the negativity.

Lama Zopa Rinpoche advises:

“If you want others to love you, you must first love others. If you benefit others, naturally they will benefit you. The cause and effect of karma is as simple as this. The Vajrasattva purification practice, which is more powerful than negative karma, can prevent you from experiencing the problems that negative karma would otherwise bring you. Thus, the practice of purification is one of the most important solutions to our problems and is extremely necessary, even for people who believe that we have only one life. If you don’t want relationship problems, business failures, illnesses such as cancer or AIDS, notoriety, or the criticism of others, the practice of Vajrasattva is extremely important – both for those who accept the existence of reincarnation and karma, and for those who do not.”

events.description:
We lead this practice online and in person at the centre.
For online meetings we use the tool called Zoom. There are two options:
1. Use the Zoom app. If you haven’t used it before it will be downloaded to your phone or computer.
2. Use Zoom in your web browser. In this scenario you don’t need to download the Zoom app as the meeting will open directly in your browser. (Might not work so well on your smartphone)
Read more here: https://yeshenorbu.se/online-mind-training-centre/
--------------------------
Vajrasattva is the embodiment of the purifying powers of the Buddha. Its practice enables us to cleanse all the negativities we have accumulated in countless lives and thus avoid their results of suffering and obstacles.

Vajrasattva Practice is not only about reciting mantras and visualization, but it is about purifying our minds. In the Vajrasattva Practice, we do the practice of Four Opponent Powers, which is a psychological process of purifying nonvirtous imprints on the mindstream.

They are: 1) the power of the object, taking refuge in the Three Rare Sublime Ones and generating bodhicitta; 2) the power of regret, feeling deep regret for the negativity committed; 3) the power of resolve, determining not to repeat that negativity; and 4) the power of remedy, a practice such as Vajrasattva that effectively acts as an antidote to the negativity.

Lama Zopa Rinpoche advises:

“If you want others to love you, you must first love others. If you benefit others, naturally they will benefit you. The cause and effect of karma is as simple as this. The Vajrasattva purification practice, which is more powerful than negative karma, can prevent you from experiencing the problems that negative karma would otherwise bring you. Thus, the practice of purification is one of the most important solutions to our problems and is extremely necessary, even for people who believe that we have only one life. If you don’t want relationship problems, business failures, illnesses such as cancer or AIDS, notoriety, or the criticism of others, the practice of Vajrasattva is extremely important – both for those who accept the existence of reincarnation and karma, and for those who do not.”

Donations are welcome. By donating you will help create the conditions for the teachings to be available and for supporting the centre. We thank you so much for supporting the centre.

events.name: Founders Running Club
events.description:
Running and running a company are hard--but they're both a lot easier when we do them with people we like. This club is for founders past, present & future. If you're building a company or looking to start one, we give encouragement & community.

-------------The Problem-----------

"Founder" is a lifestyle that most people can't relate to. We spend a lot of time on the roller coaster of major highs and lows. We're competitive and persistent to the point of lonliness. We need to make the best move when there are no good moves--a situation that often results in deeply unpopular decisions. To survive, we need discipline, healthy habits, and support from one another.

------------The Solution-------------

Founders have a lot to gain from running. Runners practice the self-motivation & grit required to press through momentary lows. Running sharpens competitive instincts & trains the pursuit of self improvement. It's also an intensely social sport that allows us to quickly build community. Founders Running Club is a place for founders to enjoy the benefits of running with other decision makers living the same lifestyle. It's also a place to connect to investors, super-connectors and other deal makers experiencing these challenges.

--------Event Specifics------------

Runners of all levels are welcome to join us for jogging and a beer. Mingle from 6:45-7:00. At 7:00, we break into two or three groups:

Pre-Seed: 5k @ 5:45 pace
Series A: 8k @ 5:00 pace

Now when most organisations are internally focused to cope with the covid-19 challenges it is hard to maintain and create new business. This is extremely difficult for smaller companies who already operate on thin margins and with little in the bank. At THINGS we believe the best we can do to help our members/alumni startups now is to support their efforts to fill up their sales funnels. A huge number of devices will be connected with each other in the upcoming IoT era. These devices may have different structures and functions, but one thing is in common, power is needed for these devices to connect to the Internet so that they can be monitored and controlled remotely.

While the edge devices are becoming cheaper, the cost of replacing the devices or the batteries on all these devices scattered around the globe is expensive. This calls for a smart solution to extend the lifetime of the devices with less battery charges and there are two directions in solving this problem:

Hello Crushers,

This is how the meetup is going to be structured.

1. Introduction: I'll briefly introduce the concept of Comfort Zone Challenges.

2. Talks: You’ll have the opportunity to either introduce yourself to the group, talk about their fears or what you expect to get out of this group or use this opportunity to talk about one of your passions.

3. Comfort Zone Challenges (30-60min): In groups of three everybody goes out to do challenges. If you are a rookie, your first one will be the “Lie Down Challenge” which has you lying down for 30 seconds in a crowded place (see video).

4. Roundup: After the challenges we meet up again and everybody shares his/her experience to develop strategies how to improve more the next time.

So let's get together, face challenges practically and crush our comfort zone. In the end, you should get some benefits for your everyday life, so we’ll adjust and you look at your very own comfort zone. You don’t have to share anything, that’s why the challenges are done individually (nobody from the group is looking). Everyone’s zone is different for different areas, so the challenges afterwards should be tailored for you specifically, for personal improvement.

For anyone wondering, the event is free.

events.description:
AWESOME NEWS! This will from now on be a regular thing that is hosted at the re-opened blackfrog studios in Stockholm.

We live-stream the whole event! If you can't make it, you can still watch the stream and join the chat at twitch.com/tunecasttv/

Ableton jams are pretty simple. No special hardware is required. Synchronization is very simple through Ableton Link (see below). All sounds, loops, instruments, and experience levels are welcome.

Or bring nothing and no experience at all. A relaxed attitude is all you need.

What to Bring

Gear: Laptop, sound card, a cable to plug in to the mixer, and headphones.

Also bring your favorite loops and sounds. A little prep goes a long way. If you have a bunch of stuff prepared at a certain tempo, then feel free to suggest that tempo.

How to Sync

Easy. Just connect to my home wifi and turn on ‘Link’ in Ableton (9.6 or later) Preferences. Hit play. Ableton will start playing on the next bar.

Genre

Basically ... electronic. We can experiment with a variety of tempos.

What to Play

The key is to be a bit sparse. A single instrument track is probably enough.

You don't need to be playing the entire time. Or at all. In fact, it's usually best when only 2 or 3 people are playing at once and the rest are laying out.

Also Appreciated ...

Extra cables, mixer, USB hub, MIDI interface, beer for Christian.

You can also use ...

I will bring spare MIDI keyboards for somebody to borrow. We have an extra Minilogue lying around the studio. I can also bring a Monologue, Bass Station 2, SH-101, Analog Heat, or Waldorf Streichfelt if you ask me in advance.

The focus of the book is on understanding happiness and the joy of life. There is an amazing consensus between these two spiritual statesmen and agreement on perspectives on life and how to achieve joy and happiness. They take turns reinforcing common views and perspectives. They agree that people are fundamentally good and that there are common values shared by different religions. The ability of people to forgive and carry on their lives is exemplified by the Truth and Reconciliation Commission process in South Africa, which has served as an example for other countries to undertake similar processes.

Another key message in the book is that if you are positive and warm-hearted towards other persons, they will reciprocate. A more surprising message is that joy often is realised by passing through difficulties, suffering and adversity. The expression passing through adversity is worth reflecting on. It means that adversity is a temporary phase and that you will overcome it. It is a warm and uplifting book that I hope many persons, in fact everybody, will read.

The book circle is structured in four sessions following the outline of the book.

Session 1: The nature of true Joy.

Session 2: The obstacles to Joy.

Session 3: Eight pillars of Joy; four qualities of the mind: perspective, humility, humour and acceptance.

Session 4: Eight pillars of Joy; four qualities of the heart: forgiveness, gratitude, compassion and generosity.

The book is included in the course fees.

The weekend teaching by Stephan Pende will be based on the text "The 37 Practices of a Bodhisattva". This is the second part of the Compassion Training for Rebels that Stephan held last autumn, however, if you missed the first part, you can still participate in this course.

"The 37 Practices of a Bodhisattva" was written by the 10th century Tibetan master Tokme Zongpo. It is one of the most revered texts in the Tibetan Buddhist tradition. It describes the practices and attitudes of the awakening rebel who wants to heal, grow up and wake up for the benefit of all.

Finding an authentic way to relate to traditional Buddhist practices and texts can be difficult for us in the west. The texts are incredibly powerful, but being from a different cultural context from where the practices originated, makes it difficult to move beyond intellectual understanding and perfunctory repetition towards allowing them to touch our hearts and transform our lives as they are meant to.

For those who are on the Buddhist path, finding ways to work authentically and intimately with practices and texts is very important otherwise much of our study and practice can remain disappointingly superficial. In this course, we will explore how to bring the wisdom of this text into our lives and relationships.

18:00 - 21:00 Workshop: Setting up Event-based Progressive Delivery with Keptn on k8s by

Abstract:
Workshop: Setting up Event-based Progressive Delivery with Keptn on k8s Andreas Grabner

Keptn is an open source event-based control plane for delivery and operations of cloud native application. Keptn separates the process defined by SREs (Shipyard) from the actual tooling defined by DevOps engineers (Uniform) and the artifacts provided by Dev. With Keptn you can add or update a stage or replace tools without changing a single line of pipeline code and that saves time! Keptn uses a built-in deployment scoring mechanism based on SLIs & SLOs used to enforce quality gates and to automatically validate auto-remediation in production.

Join this workshop where Andreas Grabner will guide you through

1. Setting up a GKE Cluster

2. Installing your first Keptn Control Plane

3. Have Keptn deliver a cloud native app through a multi-stage delivery pipeline

4. Have Keptn enforce quality gates based on SLIs & SLOs

5. Have Keptn enable Blue/Green for production deployments

6. Have Keptn orchestrated Auto-Remediation in production

7. Have a lot of fun with cloud native

Workshop attendees have to bring a laptop that has

1. git, gcloud & kubectl locally installed

2. access to *.cloud.google.com, *.github.com & *.dynatrace.com

We will use Free SaaS Services from Google Cloud, GitHub and Dynatrace. In preparation please

1. Sign up for a Google Cloud Account if you don’t already have one. This will create an account with an initial $300 GCP credit. If you sign up for a corporate email you can apply for an extra $200 in credit by following step 1 in this page: https://keptn.sh/docs/quickstart/setup_platform/setup_gke/

2. Sign up for a GitHub account in case you don’t have one. We will create a workshop specific GitHub repo for our Keptn project during the workshop

3. As Keptn relies on Monitoring data to enforce SLIs & SLOs we will be using the free Dynatrace SaaS Trial, one of the Keptn supported monitoring tools. Feel free to signup for a Dynatrace SaaS Trial upfront but best is a couple of days prior to the workshop as the trial by default only runs 15 Days. Signup here: http://bit.ly/dtsaastrial

Social Profiles LinkedIn: https://www.linkedin.com/in/grabnerandi/

Become skilled at applying these techniques to generate bodhichitta, the wish to attain enlightenment for the benefit of others, which is the very heart of Buddha’s teachings.

LEVEL
Intermediate

PREREQUISITE
Ideally, for participants of Discovering Buddhism program. But anyone who has some basic understanding of Buddhism is welcome to join this Module.

COURSE DESCRIPTION
What we believe in Buddhism is that we all have incredible potential. We have potential to become complete human beings. We have the potential to become really awake. By awake, we mean completely free of all disturbances of negative emotions, of harmful attitudes. We have the potential to fully develop our capacity for love, compassion and wisdom. But to be able to realise that potential we need to know methods. We need to work at developing our wisdom in order to be able to achieve this.

WHAT WILL I LEARN ON THIS COURSE
In this course you will be able to get answers to questions like these:

What do you mean by awakening?
What do you mean by enlightenment?
What is that attitude wishing to achieve, or to experience, this full awakening that’s free from suffering, with fully developed positive qualities?
What is that attitude, or that state of mind, all about?
Why would you want to do that?
Why would you want to become enlightened?
What’s the point of it?
Doesn’t sound so easy to achieve, (it isn’t so easy to achieve), so why would you want to?
What are the benefits of it?

WHAT WILL I TAKE AWAY FROM THIS COURSE INTO MY DAILY LIFE
The aspiration with this course is that participants will be able to integrate reflection skills into their daily lives. Whenever we are caught up in disturbing emotions, we can reflect on the root cause of our dissatisfaction and difficulties and apply knowledge accumulated in the course to overcome those emotions. By studying about the gradual path to awakening, we develop more conviction that we can free ourselves from suffering and help others do the same.

WHO IS TEACHING THE COURSE
Martin Ström (session 1-9)
Martin is the founder and director of Yeshe Norbu Mind Training Centre. For almost 20 years he’s been on a mission to understand more about the mind, both from a western neuro scientific and an eastern contemplative perspective. Martin is a licensed CBT Psychologist and has practiced meditation for almost two decades. He is also a graduate of the two-year program Foundation of Buddhist Thought. Among other things, Martin has taught mindfulness in the corporate world as an accredited trainer of Corporate Based Mindfulness Training. He is also the co-author of three books; Fokus på jobbet in Swedish, and I’m Sorry You Were Saying and The Mind of The Leader in English.

Venerable Michael Lobsang Yeshe (session 10-14)
Venerable Michael was born in London in 1966 to a Greek father and a Belgian mother, and was raised in Kopan Monastery in Nepal and has been a monk in the Tibetan Buddhist tradition since the age of 7. At age 13, he entered the Sera Jey Monastic University in South India where he spent the next 18 years studying Buddhist Philosophy. Since 1996, Ven Michael Yeshe has been invited to Buddhist centres in America, Singapore, Malaysia and Holland as a translator and teacher. For the last 11 years he had been residing at the Tara Institute in Melbourne where he served as translator for the Tibetan Buddhist master Venerable Geshe Doga.

Running and running a company are hard--but they're both a lot easier when we do them with people we like. This club is for founders past, present & future. If you're building a company or looking to start one, we give encouragement & community.

-------------The Problem-----------

"Founder" is a lifestyle that most people can't relate to. We spend a lot of time on the roller coaster of major highs and lows. We're competitive and persistent to the point of lonliness. We need to make the best move when there are no good moves--a situation that often results in deeply unpopular decisions. To survive, we need discipline, healthy habits, and support from one another.

------------The Solution-------------

Founders have a lot to gain from running. Runners practice the self-motivation & grit required to press through momentary lows. Running sharpens competitive instincts & trains the pursuit of self improvement. It's also an intensely social sport that allows us to quickly build community. Founders Running Club is a place for founders to enjoy the benefits of running with other decision makers living the same lifestyle. It's also a place to connect to investors, super-connectors and other deal makers experiencing these challenges.
